<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><hymn_number>283</hymn_number>
<author>Stefania Piovesan</author>
<title>Heaven above</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 I've got a question in my head:
 what do I gotta do when no one is around?
 I got some fears inside and I need a help
 from someone else, not me.
 After many many years of losing faith I learned
 my strength is like illusion
 What I need is everlasting love from above
 What I need is to know who I am
 I wanna turn tears into laughter
 What I need is to take apart
 the days when I am blue.

[V2]
 There's a heaven above
 You can't go on, when you need to be strong
 There's a heaven above
 There's an answer for your prayers
 listen what I say
 There's a heaven above
 And when around there is no one
 There's a heaven above

[V3]
 And many people use to think
 they choose to be alive
 and they will choose when to die
 for me is not the same, the possession of my days
 is matter of the Lord.

[V4]
 After many many years...

[V5]
 There's a heaven above...</lyrics>
</song>